What I&#x27;m saying is I don&#x27;t see a language where hello world is<p><pre><code>    module Main

    main = println &quot;Hello World&quot;
</code></pre>
as inferior to a language where it is<p><pre><code>    println &quot;Hello World&quot;
</code></pre>
simply because of that. That&#x27;s a particularly superficial way of looking at languages.
